verses.text_plain: Behold, the Lord maketh the earth empty, and maketh it waste, and turneth it upside down, and scattereth abroad the inhabitants thereof.
verses.verse_html:
1Behold, the Lord maketh the earth empty, and maketh it waste, and turneth it upside down, and scattereth abroad the inhabitants thereof. ▼
▼ turneth…: Heb. perverteth the face thereof

footnotes.body_text: ▼ turneth…: Heb. perverteth the face thereof
footnotes.body_html: ▼ turneth…: Heb. perverteth the face thereof

verses.text_plain: And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest; as with the servant, so with his master; as with the maid, so with her mistress; as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the lender, so with the borrower; as with the taker of usury, so with the giver of usury to him.
verses.verse_html:
2And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest; as with the servant, so with his master; as with the maid, so with her mistress; as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the lender, so with the borrower; as with the taker of usury, so with the giver of usury to him. ▼
▼ priest: or, prince

tokens.text: And it shall be, as with the people
as with the taker of usury

verses.text_plain: The land shall be utterly emptied, and utterly spoiled: for the Lord hath spoken this word.
verses.verse_html: 3The land shall be utterly emptied, and utterly spoiled: for the Lord hath spoken this word.

verses.text_plain: The earth mourneth and fadeth away, the world languisheth and fadeth away, the haughty people of the earth do languish.
verses.verse_html:
4The earth mourneth and fadeth away, the world languisheth and fadeth away, the haughty people of the earth do languish. ▼
▼ the haughty…: Heb. the height of the people

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the haughty…: Heb. the height of the people
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the haughty…: Heb. the height of the people

verses.text_plain: The earth also is defiled under the inhabitants thereof; because they have transgressed the laws, changed the ordinance, broken the everlasting covenant.
verses.verse_html: 5The earth also is defiled under the inhabitants thereof; because they have transgressed the laws, changed the ordinance, broken the everlasting covenant.

verses.text_plain: Therefore hath the curse devoured the earth, and they that dwell therein are desolate: therefore the inhabitants of the earth are burned, and few men left.
verses.verse_html: 6Therefore hath the curse devoured the earth, and they that dwell therein are desolate: therefore the inhabitants of the earth are burned, and few men left.

verses.text_plain: The new wine mourneth, the vine languisheth, all the merryhearted do sigh.
verses.verse_html: 7The new wine mourneth, the vine languisheth, all the merryhearted do sigh.

verses.text_plain: The mirth of tabrets ceaseth, the noise of them that rejoice endeth, the joy of the harp ceaseth.
verses.verse_html: 8The mirth of tabrets ceaseth, the noise of them that rejoice endeth, the joy of the harp ceaseth.

verses.text_plain: They shall not drink wine with a song; strong drink shall be bitter to them that drink it.
verses.verse_html: 9They shall not drink wine with a song; strong drink shall be bitter to them that drink it.

verses.text_plain: The city of confusion is broken down: every house is shut up, that no man may come in.
verses.verse_html: 10The city of confusion is broken down: every house is shut up, that no man may come in.

tokens.text: that no man may come in

verses.text_plain: There is a crying for wine in the streets; all joy is darkened, the mirth of the land is gone.
verses.verse_html: 11There is a crying for wine in the streets; all joy is darkened, the mirth of the land is gone.

verses.text_plain: In the city is left desolation, and the gate is smitten with destruction.
verses.verse_html: 12In the city is left desolation, and the gate is smitten with destruction.

verses.text_plain: When thus it shall be in the midst of the land among the people, there shall be as the shaking of an olive tree, and as the gleaning grapes when the vintage is done.
verses.verse_html: 13When thus it shall be in the midst of the land among the people, there shall be as the shaking of an olive tree, and as the gleaning grapes when the vintage is done.

tokens.text: When thus it shall be in the midst

verses.text_plain: They shall lift up their voice, they shall sing for the majesty of the Lord, they shall cry aloud from the sea.
verses.verse_html: 14They shall lift up their voice, they shall sing for the majesty of the Lord, they shall cry aloud from the sea.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore glorify ye the Lord in the fires, even the name of the Lord God of Israel in the isles of the sea.
verses.verse_html:
15Wherefore glorify ye the Lord in the fires, even the name of the Lord God of Israel in the isles of the sea. ▼
▼ fires: or, valleys

verses.text_plain: From the uttermost part of the earth have we heard songs, even glory to the righteous. But I said, My leanness, my leanness, woe unto me! the treacherous dealers have dealt treacherously; yea, the treacherous dealers have dealt very treacherously.
verses.verse_html:
16From the uttermost part of the earth have we heard songs, even glory to the righteous. But I said, My leanness, my leanness, woe unto me! the treacherous dealers have dealt treacherously; yea, the treacherous dealers have dealt very treacherously. ▼
▼ uttermost…: Heb. wing
 , ▼
▼ My leanness: Heb. Leanness to me, or, My secret to me

footnotes.body_text: ▼ My leanness: Heb. Leanness to me, or, My secret to me
footnotes.body_html: ▼ My leanness: Heb. Leanness to me, or, My secret to me

verses.text_plain: Fear, and the pit, and the snare, are upon thee, O inhabitant of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 17Fear, and the pit, and the snare, are upon thee, O inhabitant of the earth.

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass, that he who fleeth from the noise of the fear shall fall into the pit; and he that cometh up out of the midst of the pit shall be taken in the snare: for the windows from on high are open, and the foundations of the earth do shake.
verses.verse_html: 18And it shall come to pass, that he who fleeth from the noise of the fear shall fall into the pit; and he that cometh up out of the midst of the pit shall be taken in the snare: for the windows from on high are open, and the foundations of the earth do shake.

verses.text_plain: The earth is utterly broken down, the earth is clean dissolved, the earth is moved exceedingly.
verses.verse_html: 19The earth is utterly broken down, the earth is clean dissolved, the earth is moved exceedingly.

verses.text_plain: The earth shall reel to and fro like a drunkard, and shall be removed like a cottage; and the transgression thereof shall be heavy upon it; and it shall fall, and not rise again.
verses.verse_html: 20The earth shall reel to and fro like a drunkard, and shall be removed like a cottage; and the transgression thereof shall be heavy upon it; and it shall fall, and not rise again.

tokens.text: upon it; and it shall fall

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in that day, that the Lord shall punish the host of the high ones that are on high, and the kings of the earth upon the earth.
verses.verse_html:
21And it shall come to pass in that day, that the Lord shall punish the host of the high ones that are on high, and the kings of the earth upon the earth. ▼
▼ punish: Heb. visit upon

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in that day

footnotes.body_html: ▼ punish: Heb. visit upon

verses.text_plain: And they shall be gathered together, as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and shall be shut up in the prison, and after many days shall they be visited.
verses.verse_html:
22And they shall be gathered together, as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and shall be shut up in the prison, and after many days shall they be visited. ▼
▼ as prisoners…: Heb. with the gathering of prisoners
 , ▼
▼ pit: or, dungeon
 , ▼
▼ visited: or, found wanting

tokens.text: And they shall be gathered together

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as prisoners…: Heb. with the gathering of prisoners
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as prisoners…: Heb. with the gathering of prisoners
▼ visited: or, found wanting

verses.text_plain: Then the moon shall be confounded, and the sun ashamed, when the Lord of hosts shall reign in mount Zion, and in Jerusalem, and before his ancients gloriously.
verses.verse_html:
23Then the moon shall be confounded, and the sun ashamed, when the Lord of hosts shall reign in mount Zion, and in Jerusalem, and before his ancients gloriously. ▼
▼ before…: or, there shall be glory before his ancients

footnotes.body_text: ▼ before…: or, there shall be glory before his ancients
footnotes.body_html: ▼ before…: or, there shall be glory before his ancients
